    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-08-12T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-08-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <head>353. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Chile</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Cuba</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d353fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 611.37/8–1259. Secret; <gloss target="#t_NIACT1">Niact</gloss>.
                        Repeated to the Department as Secto 5, which is the source text.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1959-08-12T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1959—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. We cognizant problem Ambassador seeing <persName corresp="#p_CRF1"
                        >Castro</persName> explained <gloss target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss> 354
                    repeated Santiago.<note n="2" xml:id="d353fn2">
                        <ref target="#d352">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>Assume this attitude of <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> needs be
                    weighed in light [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>]
                    report that <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> peeved because Embassy
                    Havana allegedly knew of <persName corresp="#p_MGD1">Morgan</persName> invasion
                    attempt and he <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName>, not informed. This
                    seems preposterous in view information furnished Embassy Havana approximately
                    week ago re <persName corresp="#p_MGD1">Morgan</persName> and which Ambassador
                    discussed with Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_RR1">Roa</persName>.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d353fn3">See <ref target="#d348">Document 348</ref>.</note> Is
                    it correct assume that <persName corresp="#p_RR1">Roa</persName> might not have
                    had opportunity to pass information to <persName corresp="#p_CRF1"
                        >Castro</persName>?</p>
                <p>Is <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> situation so involved that he
                    may publicly denounce US and Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_BPW1"
                        >Bonsal</persName> for having withheld detailed knowledge invasion attempt
                    (which US did not have as far as <persName corresp="#p_RRRJ1"
                        >Rubottom</persName> aware) even though <persName corresp="#p_CRF1"
                        >Castro</persName> may have been informed by <persName corresp="#p_RR1"
                        >Roa</persName> of broad outline reported <persName corresp="#p_MGD1"
                        >Morgan</persName> effort several days ago.</p>
                <p>Please advise re above<note n="4" xml:id="d353fn4">No reply by the Embassy in
                        Havana has been found.</note> since may have important bearing on work of
                    conference and possible attitude Cuban delegation here. Secretary and/or
                        <persName corresp="#p_RRRJ1">Rubottom</persName> will raise subject
                    Ambassador’s inability see <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> with
                        <persName corresp="#p_RR1">Roa</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
